OL,3,CDrug driving 'shockingly prevalent'
OL,4,Cand 'exceeding' drink drive arrests
OL,6,FIt has been a decade since drug
OL,7,Fdriving became a specific offence, and
OL,8,Fsome police forces say it is now so
OL,9,Fprevalent that it is exceeding drink
OL,10,Fdriving arrests in their areas.
OL,12,FOn March 2 2015 it became an
OL,13,Findividual offence to drive with any
OL,14,Fone of 16 specific drugs (above
OL,15,Fcertain levels) in the blood. Prior to
OL,16,Fthat, police officers had to rely on
OL,17,Folder legislation around being unfit
OL,18,Fto drive if they suspected the driver
OL,19,Fwas under the influence.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/13
