OL,3,CDrug driving 'shockingly prevalent'
OL,4,Cand 'exceeding' drink drive arrests
OL,6,FHowever, arrested drivers then have to
OL,7,Fbe taken to a police station to give a
OL,8,Fblood sample, as only this can be used
OL,9,Fas evidence for prosecutions. It has
OL,10,Fto be done by a qualified nurse, and
OL,11,Fall the while, the traffic officer who
OL,12,Farrested the suspect is kept away from
OL,13,Fother duties to supervise the process.
OL,15,FThe test then has to be sent to an
OL,16,Fapproved laboratory, and it can take
OL,17,Fweeks or even months to be analysed if
OL,18,Fthere is a backlog. Sometimes, the
OL,19,Fdelay for lab results can exceed the
OL,20,Fsix-month limit on bringing a
OL,21,Fprosecution to a Magistrates Court.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/13
